free_txt: Isotope Separator Accelerator Facility
(ISAC-1) with TRIUMF-UK detector array (TUDA)
Two LEDAs were placed 19.5 and 60.5 cm
downstream of the target. A complete LEDA consisting
of eight identical sectors, segmented into 16 annular
elements, was used for the most downstream detector;
while four sectors in a cross configuration were used
for the detector that was nearer the target.
Isotope Separator Accelerator Facility
(ISAC-1) with TRIUMF-UK detector array (TUDA)
20Na5+ ions were extracted and accelerated to 1.250
and 1.600 MeV/u. The beam was bunched and delivered
in pulses separated by 86 ns.
Each LEDA was calibrated through use of a standard
triple-alpha source containing the isotopes 239Pu,
241Am, and 244Cm.
Experimental target of (CH2)n, provided by the Centre
de Recherches du Cyclotron, Louvain-la-Neuve. This
had a thickness of about 795 microg/cm2 (+/-10%)
determined by weighing the targets and was consistent
with energy loss incurred by ions detected after
traversing the target
Error bars assume Poissonian statistical
effects only
Data taken from Fig. 6. No reply from the
main author.
